Package: RDiffPuter
Type: Package
Title: Diffusion-Based Imputation of Missing Tabular Data
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marcel", "Neunhoeffer", email = "marcel@marcel-neunhoeffer.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: An R port of the DiffPuter algorithm (Zhang et al., ICLR 2025)
    for missing-value imputation of tabular data using a diffusion model
    trained inside an Expectation-Maximisation (EM) loop. Accepts arbitrary
    data frames with continuous and categorical columns, detects missingness
    from 'NA', and runs on CPU, CUDA, or Apple Silicon (MPS) via the 'torch'
    package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    cli,
    R6,
    torch
